            "id": "4580507",
            "title": "Corning falls despite Q1 beat as Q2 sales outlook below estimates",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\">Shares of Corning (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GLW\" title=\"Corning Incorporated\">GLW</a></span>) fell about 10% premarket on Tuesday despite first-quarter results beating estimates.</p>\n<p>However, the second quarter's sales guidance of $4.6B came in below analysts' estimate of  $4.67B.</p>\n<h2>Q1 Metrics</h2>\n<p>Core sales <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/20489853-corning-announces-strong-first-quarter-2026-financial-results-1#hasComeFromMpArticle\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"jumped\">jumped</a> 18% year-over-year to about $4.35B. Core EPS surged around 30% year-over-year to $0.70. Both top and bottom line numbers <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4580485-corning-non-gaap-eps-of-0_70-beats-by-0_01-revenue-of-4_35b-beats-by-40m\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"beat\">beat</a> analysts' expectations.</p>\n<p>\"Additionally, we finalized two more hyperscaler deals similar in size and duration to our recently announced multiyear, up-to-$6 billion agreement with Meta. In total, we have powerful momentum across our Market-Access Platforms,\" said Chairman, President and CEO Wendell Weeks. \"Based on strong demand for our innovations, we plan to upgrade and extend our Springboard plan through 2030 at our May 6 investor event. We will introduce our new Photonics Market-Access Platform and explain the underlying technical and demand trends driving our Gen AI product development.\"</p>\n<p>First quarter net sales from the Optical Communications unit soared 36% year-over-year to around $1.85B.</p>\n<p>The company created a Glass Innovations segment, combining its former Display and Specialty Materials segments. Sales from this unit grew 1% year-over-year to $1.42B.</p>\n<p>Net sales from its Automotive unit fell 1% year-over-year to $437M. Meanwhile, net sales from the Solar unit surged 80% year-over-year to $370M.</p>\n<h2>Outlook</h2>\n<p>Corning said that for the second quarter, management expects to grow core sales about 14% year over year to about $4.6B, versus a <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GLW/earnings/estimates?period=quarterly\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"consensus\">consensus</a> estimate of $4.67B.</p>\n<p>The company said the second-quarter guidance includes an extended maintenance shutdown at Corning’s solar wafer facility, including the transition to a permanent power system while the company repairs, upgrades, and modifies production equipment to increase throughput in future quarters. This will cause an additional $30M of expense in the second quarter versus the first quarter and is included in guidance, the company added.</p>\n<p>Corning expects core EPS to grow about 25% year over year to a range of $0.73 to $0.77 (midpoint at $0.75) versus a consensus estimate of $0.75.</p>\n<h3> More on Corning</h3>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
            "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/assets/og_image_1200-29b2bfe1a595477db6826bd2126c63ac2091efb7ec76347a8e7f81ba17e3de6c.png",
