            "id": "4580519",
            "title": "Evercore leads all large-cap financial stocks in YoY CapEx growth",
            "description": "<html><body><p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\" data-eci=\"true\">Capital expenditure growth is a key indicator of how aggressively a company is investing in its future, whether through new infrastructure, equipment, technology, or capacity expansion.</p>\n<p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">The following list ranks U.S. large-cap financials stocks by their year-over-year CapEx growth percentage, offering a data-driven look at which companies are putting the most capital to work relative to the prior year.</p>\n<p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">Below is a list of 10 U.S. financials stocks ranked according to their year-over-year capital expenditure growth percentage. The list spans multiple sub-sectors within financials, including Investment Banking and Brokerage, Life and Health Insurance, Asset Management and Custody Banks, Consumer Finance, Property and Casualty Insurance, Transaction &amp; Payment Processing Services, and Financial Exchanges and Data.</p>\n<p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">Evercore (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/EVR\" title=\"Evercore Inc.\">EVR</a>) tops the list with a CapEx growth rate of 145.85% year-over-year, investing $74 million in capital expenditures in fiscal 2025, a 145.8% jump from the prior year, as the independent investment bank expanded its office infrastructure and technology platforms off the back of a record $3.9 billion in revenue, itself up 29.4% year-over-year.</p>\n<p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">Globe Life (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GL\" title=\"Globe Life Inc.\">GL</a>) and Blackstone (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BX\" title=\"Blackstone Inc.\">BX</a>) follow in second and third place with growth rates of 100.55% and 88.41% respectively, while American Express (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/AXP\" title=\"American Express Company\">AXP</a>) and W. R. Berkley (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/WRB\" title=\"W. R. Berkley Corporation\">WRB</a>) round out the top five at 61.28% and 60.94%.<span class=\"citation-nbsp\"></span><span class=\"citation inline\"></span></p>\n<p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">Fidelity National Information Services (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/FIS\" title=\"Fidelity National Information Services, Inc.\">FIS</a>) and S&amp;P Global (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SPGI\" title=\"S&amp;P Global Inc.\">SPGI</a>) occupy the sixth and seventh positions with CapEx growth of 58.76% and 57.26%, while SoFi Technologies (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SOFI\" title=\"SoFi Technologies, Inc.\">SOFI</a>) and BlackRock (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BLK\" title=\"BlackRock, Inc.\">BLK</a>) follow at 57.16% and 47.06%.</p>\n<p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">Principal Financial Group (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/PFG\" title=\"Principal Financial Group, Inc.\">PFG</a>) rounds out the list at 42.44%, having delivered 13% non-GAAP EPS growth and $1.81 trillion in assets under administration in fiscal 2025.</p>\n<p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">Globe Life (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GL\" title=\"Globe Life Inc.\">GL</a>) is the sole Strong Buy at 4.57 according to Seeking Alpha Quant ratings, the only such rating across the entire screen, while Blackstone (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BX\" title=\"Blackstone Inc.\">BX</a>), FIS, and S&amp;P Global (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SPGI\" title=\"S&amp;P Global Inc.\">SPGI</a>) all carry Sell ratings at 2.24, 2.30, and 2.25 respectively, creating an unusual dynamic where three of the list's heaviest-spending names are also the quant model's least-favored picks.<span class=\"citation-nbsp\"></span><span class=\"citation inline\"></span></p>\n<p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">Here is the list:</p>\n<ol class=\"marker:text-quiet list-decimal pl-8\">\n<li class=\"py-0 my-0 prose-p:pt-0 prose-p:mb-2 prose-p:my-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:pt-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:mb-2 [&amp;&gt;p]:my-0\"><p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">Evercore Inc. (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/EVR\" title=\"Evercore Inc.\">EVR</a>), CapEx growth YoY: 145.85%</p></li>\n<li class=\"py-0 my-0 prose-p:pt-0 prose-p:mb-2 prose-p:my-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:pt-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:mb-2 [&amp;&gt;p]:my-0\"><p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">Globe Life Inc. (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GL\" title=\"Globe Life Inc.\">GL</a>), CapEx growth YoY: 100.55%</p></li>\n<li class=\"py-0 my-0 prose-p:pt-0 prose-p:mb-2 prose-p:my-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:pt-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:mb-2 [&amp;&gt;p]:my-0\"><p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">Blackstone Inc. (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BX\" title=\"Blackstone Inc.\">BX</a>), CapEx growth YoY: 88.41%</p></li>\n<li class=\"py-0 my-0 prose-p:pt-0 prose-p:mb-2 prose-p:my-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:pt-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:mb-2 [&amp;&gt;p]:my-0\"><p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">American Express Company (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/AXP\" title=\"American Express Company\">AXP</a>), CapEx growth YoY: 61.28%</p></li>\n<li class=\"py-0 my-0 prose-p:pt-0 prose-p:mb-2 prose-p:my-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:pt-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:mb-2 [&amp;&gt;p]:my-0\"><p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">W. R. Berkley Corporation (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/WRB\" title=\"W. R. Berkley Corporation\">WRB</a>), CapEx growth YoY: 60.94%</p></li>\n<li class=\"py-0 my-0 prose-p:pt-0 prose-p:mb-2 prose-p:my-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:pt-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:mb-2 [&amp;&gt;p]:my-0\"><p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">Fidelity National Information Services, Inc. (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/FIS\" title=\"Fidelity National Information Services, Inc.\">FIS</a>), CapEx growth YoY: 58.76%</p></li>\n<li class=\"py-0 my-0 prose-p:pt-0 prose-p:mb-2 prose-p:my-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:pt-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:mb-2 [&amp;&gt;p]:my-0\"><p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">S&amp;P Global Inc. (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SPGI\" title=\"S&amp;P Global Inc.\">SPGI</a>), CapEx growth YoY: 57.26%</p></li>\n<li class=\"py-0 my-0 prose-p:pt-0 prose-p:mb-2 prose-p:my-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:pt-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:mb-2 [&amp;&gt;p]:my-0\"><p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">SoFi Technologies, Inc. (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SOFI\" title=\"SoFi Technologies, Inc.\">SOFI</a>), CapEx growth YoY: 57.16%</p></li>\n<li class=\"py-0 my-0 prose-p:pt-0 prose-p:mb-2 prose-p:my-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:pt-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:mb-2 [&amp;&gt;p]:my-0\"><p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">BlackRock, Inc. (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BLK\" title=\"BlackRock, Inc.\">BLK</a>), CapEx growth YoY: 47.06%</p></li>\n<li class=\"py-0 my-0 prose-p:pt-0 prose-p:mb-2 prose-p:my-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:pt-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:mb-2 [&amp;&gt;p]:my-0\"><p class=\"my-2 [&amp;+p]:mt-4 [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:inline-block [&amp;_strong:has(+br)]:pb-2\">Principal Financial Group, Inc. (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/PFG\" title=\"Principal Financial Group, Inc.\">PFG</a>), CapEx growth YoY: 42.44%</p></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Financials ETFs: (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/XLF\" title=\"State Street Financial Sel Sec SPDR ETF\">XLF</a></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/VFH\" title=\"Vanguard Financials Index Fund ETF\">VFH</a></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/IYF\" title=\"iShares US Financials ETF\">IYF</a></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/FNCL\" title=\"Fidelity MSCI Financials Index ETF\">FNCL</a></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/IYG\" title=\"iShares US Financial Services ETF\">IYG</a></span>), and (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/FXO\" title=\"First Trust Financials AlphaDEX Fund ETF\">FXO</a></span>)</p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
