            "id": "4580489",
            "title": "Rithm Capital stock edges up on strong Q1 segment revenues",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\">Rithm Capital (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/RITM\" title=\"Rithm Capital Corp.\">RITM</a></span>) was trading higher as the mortgage REIT's <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/20489710-rithm-capital-corp-announces-first-quarter-2026-results\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Q1 earnings\">Q1 earnings</a> exceeded analyst expectations, recording growth in mortgage origination and servicing, residential lending, and asset management.</p>\n<p>Shares were 1.48% higher at $10.27 during Tuesday pre-market trading.</p>\n<p>The New York-based company posted Q1 non-GAAP EPS of $0.51, which exceeds the S&amp;P Cap IQ consensus estimate of $0.50 but lags the prior-quarter figure of $0.74.</p>\n<p>Revenue of $1.38B surpasses the consensus of $1.27B and the prior-quarter figure of $1.29B.</p>\n<p>Rithm's multichannel mortgage origination and servicing platform, Newrez, posted a pretax operating income of $273.7M, compared to $249.1M in the fourth quarter of 2025.</p>\n<p>The residential transitional lending platform, Genesis Capital, recorded origination volume of $1.6B.</p>\n<p>Rithm Asset Management, the alternative asset management platform primarily including Sculptor Capital Management and Crestline Management, ended the quarter with $59B in assets under management, compared to the year-ago $35B.</p>\n<p>The company said its recently-acquired office properties operator, Paramount Group or Elecor Properties, witnessed continued leasing momentum with New York City lease occupancy increasing by 4.7% year-over-year.</p>\n<p>\"Despite a challenging and volatile market environment, Rithm delivered strong Q1 results, with Newrez generating a 19% annualized operating ROE, Genesis posting 80% year-over-year origination growth, and our asset management platform growing to ~$60B in AUM,\" said CEO Michael Nierenberg.</p>\n<p>Book value per common share stood at $12.51, below the consensus estimate of $12.82.</p>\n<p>Earnings call is scheduled for Tuesday, April 28, 8:00 AM ET.</p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
